				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Well, I too have gone to qeynos on varous trips to hunt trumpy iron-toe. No you do not need any other quest done first to get the bloodforge hammer, You do need to have good faction, he needs to judge you amiable or warmly...the trick to this quest is avoiding the corrupt gaurds...as i found out one very long day...it all started when I was in freeport, i decided it would be fun to do the bloodforge hammer quest and make some extra pp. So i headed off to qeynos (im still bound in greater faydark, my homeland). So i travel for 1.5-2 hours to arrive at qeynos and there he was! in the bar, Now i figured his beer buddies wouldnt like it too much if their friend was killed in front of them so i watched him once and observed his pattern. So after 15 minutes i saw trumpy my old pal, walk out of the bar, he had just stepped into the gate of the boat yard when i decided to strike...that was my mistake and somthing i tell people to watch out for,. he seems to have a friend, not sure of his name, who looks like a monk with gold armor chest plate and a wooden club. He couldnt let his friend die so he ran to the rescue, to my dismay. Now, im lvl 15 at the time and he was conning red so i made a run for it, apparently the corrupt guild club was having their annual poker tournement not to far away and they decided to put the cards down and chase after me. Well I jumped in the water hoping the gaurds heavy armor would weigh them down and render them un-able to swim. I was wrong. I was also dead. Be WARY of Trumpy's friends.
				</font>
